(a) Charge on Capacitor, $\mathrm{Q}_{\mathrm{i}}=\mathrm{CV}$
After inserting dielectric of dielectric constant $=\mathrm{k}$
$\mathrm{Q}_{\mathrm{f}}=(\mathrm{kC}) \mathrm{V}$
Induced charges on dielectric
$$
\begin{aligned}
Q_{\text {ind }} & =Q_{f}-Q_{i}=k C V-C V \\
& =(k-1) C V=\left(\frac{5}{3}-1\right) \times 90 p F \times 20 \mathrm{~V}=1.2 \mathrm{nC}
\end{aligned}
$$

(d) If $a_{M_{1}}>a_{M_{2}}$ then $M_{1}$ hits the floor before $M_{2}$
$$
\begin{aligned}
& \text { i.e. } \quad \frac{M_{1} g-Q_{1} E}{M_{1}}>\frac{M_{2} g-Q_{2} E}{M_{2}} \\
& \mathrm{~g}-\frac{\mathrm{Q}_{1} \mathrm{E}}{\mathrm{M}_{1}}>\mathrm{g}-\frac{\mathrm{Q}_{2} \mathrm{E}}{\mathrm{M}_{2}} \Rightarrow \frac{Q_{2} E}{M_{2}}>\frac{\mathrm{Q}_{1} \mathrm{E}}{\mathrm{M}_{1}} \\
& M_{1} Q_{2}>M_{2} Q_{1}
\end{aligned}
$$

(b) $W=U_{f}-U_{i}=\frac{q^{2}}{2}\left(\frac{1}{C_{f}}-\frac{1}{C_{i}}\right)\left(\because \mathrm{U}=\frac{\mathrm{q}^{2}}{2 \mathrm{C}}\right)$
$$
\begin{aligned}
& =\frac{\left(5 \times 10^{-6}\right)^{2}}{2}\left(\frac{1}{2}-\frac{1}{5}\right) \times 10^{6} \\
& =3.75 \times 10^{-6} \mathrm{~J}
\end{aligned}
$$

(a) If the charge on a spherical conductor of radius $R$ is $Q$, then electric field at distance $r$ from centre is
$$
\begin{array}{ll}
\mathrm{E}=0 & (\text { if } r \angle R) \\
E=\frac{1}{4 \pi \in_{0}} \frac{Q}{r^{2}} & (\text { if } r \geq R)
\end{array}
$$
Electric field at a distance 15 cm from the centre of sphere will be
$$
\begin{aligned}
& E=\frac{9 \times 10^{9} \times 3.2 \times 10^{-7}}{225 \times 10^{-4}} \\
& =0.128 \times 10^{6}=1.28 \times 10^{5} \mathrm{~N} / \mathrm{C}
\end{aligned}
$$
